# Project Runtimes & Commands

This project uses Docker and Node.js for management and documentation.

## Docker & Docker Compose

- Use the `node` container for documentation tasks.
- The project is running in Docker containers.

## Common NPM Commands

- `npm run install:docs`: Install Docusaurus dependencies.
- `npm run dev`: Start Docusaurus development server.
- `npm run build`: Build the documentation for production.
- `npm run start`: Start the built site.
- `npm run format`: Format the code.

## Running Commands in Docker

When performing documentation tasks, prefer executing inside the Node container if needed:

```bash
docker-compose exec node npm run build
```
